<div class='commentbox'>
There is a new strainer on the Concord this weekend. It is at the bottom of the island and reaches<br/>
most of the way across the river. The wave that is in the right channel that everyone likes to surf<br/>
is blocked by the tree. The best route is to go left of the island; there is a channel next to the<br/>
tree that is clear. It would appear that the tree is probably not moving anytime soon unless we get<br/>
more rain and the river comes up again. It would not take much to block the channel that is now<br/>
open. Kevin Lindberg </div>
</td>
